FBIS4-61295 "drsov087_a_94027" FBIS-SOV-94-087 Daily Report 5 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Moscow To Help Upgrade Indian Fighters Moscow To Help Upgrade Indian Fighters LD0505075394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0700 GMT 5 May 94 LD0505075394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] India has finally decided to upgrade, with Russia's assistance, the MiG-21 bis fighters of the Indian Air Force. This was stated by M. Mallikarjun, India's Minister of State for Defense, in parliament in Delhi. He said talks with Russia on this issue had ended and that a relevant protocol of intention had been signed.
